Supplementary 1. Description of the data

A. Distribution of ES

df_main$outlier_pre_post = ifelse(is_outlier(df_main$yi - df_main$yi_p), df_main$ID_out, NA_character_)
df_main$outlier = ifelse(is_outlier(df_main$yi), df_main$ID_out, NA_character_)
df_plot = df_main %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(yi, yi_p), names_to = "es_type", values_to = "smd") 
df_plot$es_type[df_plot$es_type=="yi"] <- "Pre-post SMD"
df_plot$es_type[df_plot$es_type=="yi_p"] <- "Post SMD"
df_plot$ID = rep(1:(nrow(df_plot)/2), each = 2)
df_plot$Outcome = df_plot$outcome_dich
df_plot$Outcome[df_plot$Outcome=="interoception"] <- "Interoception"
df_plot$Outcome[df_plot$Outcome=="symptoms"] <- "Symptoms"
ggplot(df_plot, aes(x = Outcome, y = smd)) + 
  geom_violin(aes(fill = Outcome, alpha = 0.3)) +
   geom_boxplot(width=0.1)+
  geom_jitter(aes(fill = Outcome), binaxis='y', stackdir='center', dotsize=0.4, alpha = 0.2, position=position_jitter(0.05)) + 
  facet_grid(es_type ~ "") +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(y = "SMD value") +
  theme(text = element_text(size = 18),
        legend.position = "none",
        axis.title.y = element_text(size=20, face="bold"), 
        axis.title.x = element_text(size=20, face="bold")) +
  coord_flip()

Supplementary 2. Main analysis

A. Results

V.SCE  <- impute_covariance_matrix(vi = df_main$vi, 
                                   cluster = df_main$study_ID, 
                                   r = 0.8,
                                   return_list = FALSE,
                                   smooth_vi = TRUE,
                                   subgroup = df_main$outcome_dich)

# all.equal(df$vi, diag(unlist(V.SCE)))

metafor.SCE <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,
                               mods =  ~ outcome_dich - 1,
                               data = df_main,
                               random = ~ outcome_dich | study_ID,
                               struct = "DIAG",
                               sparse = TRUE)

res.main = coef_sand(model = metafor.SCE, 
                     vcov = "CR2", cluster = df_main$study_ID)
## Joining, by = c("outcome", "beta", "SE", "df")
res.main$outcome = c("Interoception", "Symptoms")
res.main[,2:ncol(res.main)] = round(res.main[,2:ncol(res.main)], 3)

kbl(res.main) %>%
  kable_classic()
outcome beta SE tstat df p_Satt CI_L CI_U
Interoception 0.390 0.119 3.267 9.123 0.010 0.121 0.660
Symptoms 0.526 0.135 3.903 9.301 0.003 0.223 0.829

Supplementary 3. Additional analyses

A. Using a RVE approach

res.S1 <- robumeta::robu(yi ~ outcome_dich - 1, 
                            data = df_main, 
                            studynum = study_ID, 
                            var.eff.size = vi,
                            modelweights = "CORR",
                            small = TRUE,
                            rho = 0.8)$reg_table

kbl(res.S1) %>%

D. Publication bias

Square root of the eff. sample size

df_main$inv_N = with(df_main, 1/n_cases + 1/n_controls)
df_main$sqrt_inv_N = sqrt(df_main$inv_N)

sse.1 <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,
                         mods =  ~ 1 + sqrt_inv_N,
                         data = df_main,
                         random = ~ outcome_dich | study_ID,
                         struct = "DIAG",
                         sparse = TRUE)

res.S4 = coef_sand(model = sse.1, vcov = "CR2", cluster = df_main$study_ID)
## Joining, by = c("outcome", "beta", "SE", "df")
res.S4[,2:ncol(res.S4)] = round(res.S4[,2:ncol(res.S4)], 3)

kbl(res.S4) %>%
  kable_classic()
outcome beta SE tstat df p_Satt CI_L CI_U
intrcpt 0.258 0.417 0.619 5.772 0.560 -0.771 1.287
sqrt_inv_N 0.879 1.824 0.482 4.159 0.654 -4.110 5.868

Square root of the eff. sample size + mod

sse.2 <- metafor::rma.mv(yi = yi, V = V.SCE,
                         mods =  ~ - 1 + sqrt_inv_N + outcome_dich,
                         data = df_main,
                         random = ~ outcome_dich | study_ID,
                         struct = "DIAG",
                         control=list(optimizer="optim", optmethod="Nelder-Mead"),
                         sparse = TRUE)

res.sse.2 = coef_sand(model = sse.2, vcov = "CR2", cluster = df_main$study_ID)
## Joining, by = c("outcome", "beta", "SE", "df")
res.sse.2[,2:ncol(res.sse.2)] = round(res.sse.2[,2:ncol(res.sse.2)], 3)

kbl(res.sse.2) %>%
  kable_classic()

res.tot = bind_rows(
  res.main,
  res.S1,
  res.S2,
  res.S3,
  res.S4[2,],
  res.S5,
  res.S6)[,1:(ncol(res.main))]

res.tot = data.frame(
  Analysis = rep(c("Main analysis", "RVE approach", "Post-test SMD", "Alternative correlation",
                   "Small study effects", "Low RoB studies", "No imputed-SD studies"), times = c(2,2,2,2,1,2,2)),
  res.tot)

res.tot$n_exp = c(rep(c(N_main_inter_exp,N_main_sympt_exp), times = 2),
                  rep(c(N_S2_inter_exp,N_S2_sympt_exp), times = 1),
